  The damages caused by toxic releases from power supply 
sources burning high-sulfur fuel (around 20,000) [sic] were 
evaluated using procedures presented in [6-8]. The calculation 
results are shown in Table 6. 
  Considering that a tendency for land prices to increase is 
being observed, the amount of the damages will also grow. 
Consequently when planning and building power supply sources, we 
need to consider the damages inflicted both on the environment 
and on human health. For practical purposes the latter factor is 
not yet reflected in the procedural recommendations for 
calculating damages. 
